        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): show cron job model selection",
        "body": "Related: #93507\r\n\r\n## What Problem This Solves\r\nFixes an issue where users creating cron jobs from the Web UI quick-create flow could not choose a model, and existing cron jobs did not make their configured/default model visible in the job list/details.\r\n\r\n## Why This Change Was Made\r\nThis reuses the existing cron `payload.model` / Control UI `payloadModel` contract instead of adding runtime or schema behavior. The quick-create wizard now accepts the same model suggestions already loaded for the advanced cron form, maps the selected value into the cron form patch for agent-turn cron jobs, and scheduled agent jobs show either the configured model or an explicit default label in both the row chips and job detail section.\r\n\r\nSilent quick-create jobs save a `systemEvent` payload, so the model selector is hidden for that preset and the patch conversion does not emit `payloadModel` for silent jobs.\r\n\r\n## User Impact\r\nUsers can choose a model while creating a cron job from the guided Web UI flow, and can inspect scheduled agent jobs at a glance to see which model they will use. Jobs that use the default model now say so explicitly. Silent jobs no longer present a model choice that would be ignored during save.\r\n\r\n## Evidence\r\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/cron-quick-create.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/cron.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/cron.test.ts` passed: 3 files, 63 tests.\r\n- `node_modules\\.bin\\oxfmt.CMD --check ui\\src\\ui\\views\\cron-quick-create.ts ui\\src\\ui\\views\\cron-quick-create.node.test.ts ui\\src\\ui\\views\\cron.test.ts` passed.\r\n- `git diff --check` passed.\r\n- `PYTHONUTF8=1 python .agents\\skills\\autoreview\\scripts\\autoreview --mode commit --commit HEAD` passed with `autoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported` on commit `62437b81f7d48c5a72ffcfeaad700d930b4bb57d`.\r\n- Added regression coverage that silent/systemEvent quick-create presets do not map `payloadModel` and do not render the quick-create model input.\r\n- Mocked Control UI / Playwright proof passed with the real Vite Control UI, a mocked Gateway, and system Chrome. Proof JSON: https://gist.github.com/ly85206559/d24a74e8dd7818dc34c1da6ba7d66a24\r\n- Playwright proof confirmed the existing cron row and detail both show `Model: openai/gpt-5.2` for an agentTurn job.\r\n- Playwright proof confirmed the quick-create How step accepts `openai/gpt-5.5` and the captured `cron.add` request includes `payload.model: openai/gpt-5.5`.\r\n- Playwright proof reported `pageErrors: []`.\r\n- Local visual artifacts generated for inspection: `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/cron-model-proof/01-job-list-model.png`, `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/cron-model-proof/02-quick-create-model.png`, and `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/cron-model-proof/page@5d408e05bab85b27a18d6dd4d4094162.webm`.\r\n<img width=\"1280\" height=\"912\" alt=\"01-job-list-model\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/204353ee-d065-4b4a-8b9d-1c250387a8ee\" />\r\n<img width=\"1280\" height=\"900\" alt=\"02-quick-create-model\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2ab96a85-7746-412b-a5d9-c100e50f6e75\" />\r\n",
        "branch": "codex/fix-cron-model-ui",
